t%2C%20but%20we%20still%20have%20two%20mortgages%20to%20pay%20off%20and%20three%20children%20to%20support%20for%20at%20least%20another%2016%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20our%2050s%20are%20approaching%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20early%20retirement%20doesn't%20yet%20seem%20feasible%20for%20us%20financially.%20I%20also%20like%20having%20regular%20paychecks%20coming%20in%20and%20knowing%20that%20I'm%20building%20a%20nest%20egg%2C%20not%20just%20making%20enough%20to%20get%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20me%20would%20be%20concerned%20about%20running%20out%20of%20money%20if%20I%20stopped%20working%20too%20early%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20impossible%20to%20predict%20future%20issues%20and%20hardships%20my%20family%20could%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20I'd%20prefer%20for%20us%20to%20pay%20off%20both%20of%20our%20properties%20(or%20sell%20one%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20other)%20before%20considering%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2275be3c93-e455-4b8b-862d-2cc235bd9c67%5C%22%3EOverall%2C%20I%20understand%20why%20others%20might%20want%20to%20retire%20early%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20sound%20like%20a%20dream%20to%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20in%20my%2040s%2C%20and%20maybe%20I'll%20change%20my%20mind%20in%20the%20next%20decade.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20retiring%20early%20isn't%20a%20goal%20of%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20early%20retirement%20works%20well%20for%20people%20who%20have%20hobbies%20that%20keep%20them%20busy%20and%20fulfilled%2C%20and%20those%20who%20don't%20really%20enjoy%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20writing%20is%20my%20passion%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20stop%20getting%20paid%20to%20do%20it.%20I%20can%20completely%20understand%20why%20others%20might%20want%20to%20retire%20early%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20admit%20that%20my%20ideal%20retirement%20probably%20looks%20quite%20different%20from%20other%20people's.%20I%20picture%20my%20husband%20and%20me%20living%20in%20a%20home%20we